      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "I was wondering myself.\n\nFrom the docs:\n\n> MCELL_FEOL_MK and YMTP_MK are dedicated for MTP cell implant, which is drawn by IP vendor. These layers are not supported in PDK of this version update.\n\n\"AI\" says:\n\n> \"GlobalFoundries MTP cell implant\"\n> refers to the use of a Multiple-Time Programmable (MTP) memory cell, often involving a well implant process, within GlobalFoundries' semiconductor manufacturing platforms.\n\n> eMemory's NeoMTP: This is a specific MTP solution that integrates with GlobalFoundries' manufacturing. Its second-generation (G2) version, for example, can be used in the 130nm BCD platform to achieve high reliability for automotive applications.\n\nWhich leads to https://www.ememory.com.tw/en-US/Products/MTP/NeoMTP\n\nWith this offering:\n\n> eMemory\u2019s Reprogrammable NeoMTP Qualified on GLOBALFOUNDRIES\u2019 130nm BCDLite\u00ae and BCD Technology Platforms for Automotive Applications",
